<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 9:02PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Increased Fire Danger is Expected Saturday Afternoon...
The combination of sustained winds of 15 to 20 mph, gusts of 20 to
30 mph, relative humidities dropping to 20 to 25 percent, and
decreasing fuel moisture will produce an increased fire danger
Saturday afternoon. These conditions could start as early as the
late morning, and could conclude as late as the early evening.
Please refer to your local burn permitting authorities on whether
you can burn Saturday. Use extreme caution when burning as fires
may get out of hand quickly in these conditions. Ensure fire
suppression is readily available.</description>
